0. maintain lessons.md

1. Core: intelligence is made of three core abilities. They are the spontaneous predicting ability, the reactive predicting ability and the ability to gain from the prediction. In this agent design, this is expressed by valuing three modules: the Reactionm Prediction and evaluation modules.
2. The purpose of this project is to make an agent that we can evaluate their three abilities seperately, while being able to switch backbone models and prompts for each part easily. In the end, we will find out what model + prompt works the best for each module. 
3. There are two different transportation of information. Intermodule and intramodule. Intramodule communication follows the rules stated in self.md, while intermodule communication follows the rules in the rulebook.md within each module. 
4. There are 5 module families (classes) which I will refer to as families from now on. Each have its main and sub-modules. Apart from the main module, each sub-module should be able to add or drop dynamically. Giving the agent flexible abilities.
They are: <Pr> Prediction/plan module
          <Re> Reaction/input module
          <Ev> Evaluation/action module
          <Me> Memory/logging module
          <Mo> Motor/output module
5. The self.md describes how the entire agent works, which is divided in parts. One for the entire agent, and one for each family. The agent also holds three functions regarding self.md. These are: (1)load_all: loads the whole self.md, (2) load_part: loads parts of self.md, (3) write_part: writes to a part of self.md, this requires a permission check that is maintained in interface/permissions.py. This permission may be changed during runtime. The main idea is that each family can edit the part of self that describes it. The prediction/plan family, being the main intelligence piece, default has the permission to change anything in the project, and thus have the permission to write_part any part.  
6. 申告制: When a sub-module is added, it sould follow a protocal and tell the main module what it is used for and how to use it. The main module of the family then broadcasts to all modules about the new ability after it updates the part of its family in self.md.
7. All intermodule communication goes through a bus in the agent with a format that needs to be strictly followed. The format is defined in interface/bus.py. It includes: (1) the messageID, (2) the parent messageID that triggers this message, (3) a timecode maintained by the system for resource management purpose, (4) the context, (5) the body, (6) the sender, (7) the receiver, and (8) resources.
8. The messageID follows a naming rule. Each family holds a counter for how many message it sent, the messageID is the 2 letter family name + 8 digit counter + path name. The path name is an one letter representation for common cognition paths described below.
9. Paths: P path - <Ev>-><Pr>-><Ev>-><Mo> or <Me>
          R path - <Re>-><Mo>
          E path - <Re>-><Ev>
          U path - <Re>-><Pr>
          D path - <Pr>-><Re> or <Ev> or <Mo> or <Me>
10. The agent system manages three kind of resources: (1) token ount, (2) thinking time, and (3) RAM, we don't limit and track these resources until stage3 in this project.
11. For each family and the agent system itself, there will be states. For starters, there will only be two types of states: [idle, thinking]. The main module of each agent should be able to add new states themselves in the future. (of course they will need to broadcast that they added a new state to inform other families). The states of each family will be indicated by the workload (work queued in working stack, compared to the resource each family have) and updated automatically. The state of the agent system will be indicated by the overall workload / resource.
12. Each main module should asyncronously provide functions for other modules to:
    (1) get current amount of resource in family
    (2) get task queue information (length, maxlength, resource required, estimated time)
    (3) change prompt / restart module / change model
    (4) get limit of family (context max token size, etc)
    (5) and other family specific functions, such as the speak function in <Mo>, or memory search in <Me>
    (6) signal to pause work and answer questions
    each are locked behind permission management, you need to ask <Pr> to ask for you or give you permission if you really need to. (these should be written in self.md)
13. Each module should be able to access everything within its reigon (folder)
14. Log everything. What and when each module is doing, each thought and each message sent.
